This paper involves the analysis of social media data (Twitter) to study food consumption patterns, which falls under the category of social media analysis (cs.SI). The paper also involves the use of demographic variables and machine learning models to predict obesity and diabetes statistics, which falls under the category of cyber-physical systems (cs.CYBER) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the social nature of obesity and the use of social networks, which falls under the category of social networks (cs.SOC) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
